"title": "4458: grape",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4458",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Fruit which grows in clusters on a vine. It was very widely cultivated in the Near East in biblical times and was used mostly for making wine.</p>\n<h2>The cultivation of grapes indicative of rich and fertile land</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:2-Num20:5\">NUM 20:2–20:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:21-Num13:25\">NUM 13:21–13:25</a></p>\n<h2>The failure of the grape harvest indicative of misfortune or disaster</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:10-Isa32:13\">ISA 32:10–32:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:13\">JER 8:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:1\">MIC 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:16-Hab3:19\">HAB 3:16–3:19</a></p>\n<h2>Grapes used to make wine</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:39\">DEU 28:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:9-Gen40:11\">GEN 40:9–40:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:10-Gen49:12\">GEN 49:10–49:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:15\">MIC 6:15</a></p>\n<h2>Treading grapes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:13\">AMO 9:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:27\">JDG 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:15\">NEH 13:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:30\">JER 25:30</a></p>\n<h2>Harvesting grapes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:9-Jer49:10\">JER 49:9–49:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:5\">OBA 1:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:5\">LEV 26:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:20\">NUM 13:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:8-Isa62:9\">ISA 62:8–62:9</a></p>\n<h2>Regulations concerning the grape harvest</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:10\">LEV 19:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:1-Lev25:7\">LEV 25:1–25:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:24\">DEU 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:21\">DEU 24:21</a></p>\n<h2>Dried grapes: raisins</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:11-1Sam30:12\">1SA 30:11–30:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:14-1Sam25:19\">1SA 25:14–25:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:17-2Sam6:19\">2SA 6:17–6:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:1-1Chr16:3\">1CH 16:1–16:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:1-2Sam16:2\">2SA 16:1–16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:38-1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:38–12:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:5\">SNG 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos3:1\">HOS 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>Nazirites were forbidden to consume grapes or grape products</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:1-Num6:4\">NUM 6:1–6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:14\">JDG 13:2–13:14</a></p>\n<h2>The metaphorical use of grapes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:9\">JER 6:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:32-Deut32:33\">DEU 32:32–32:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:2\">JDG 8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job15:32-Job15:34\">JOB 15:32–15:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:8-Ps80:19\">PSA 80:8–80:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:1–5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa24:5-Isa24:13\">ISA 24:5–24:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:8\">ISA 65:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer48:32\">JER 48:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:10\">HOS 9:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:12-Joel3:13\">JOL 3:12–3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:17-Rev14:20\">REV 14:17–14:20</a></p>\n<h2>The proverbial use of grapes</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:15-Matt7:16\">MAT 7:15–7:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:43-Luke6:45\">LUK 6:43–6:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:29-Jer31:30\">JER 31:29–31:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:1-Ezek18:2\">EZK 18:1–18:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:7\">1CO 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:12\">JAS 3:12</a></p>",
